ignore_max_via_stack_rule(25.10)              ignore_max_via_stack_rule(25.10)

Name
       ignore_max_via_stack_rule

Syntax
        ignore_max_via_stack_rule { true | false}

       Type: Boolean

       Default: false

       The  tech  lef file contains MAXVIASTACK syntax by default. You can use
       ignore_max_via_stack_rule  to turn  off  MAXVIASTACK  syntax  checking.
       When ignore_max_via_stack_rule  is set to true, the MAXVIASTACK rule in
       the tech lef file is ignored.

